I"÷<h2 id="review-paper-several-important-conceptions-of-martensite-phase-transition">Review paper, several important conceptions of Martensite phase transition</h2>

<p>Discuss the research result of the years.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Point group of Martensite is a sub-group of Austenite;</li>
  <li>Free energy function is a function of lattice and temperature;</li>
  <li>number of variants is relevant to the point group number;</li>
  <li>Compatible is important, especially for interface;</li>
  <li>Interface involve the material does not the energy minima;</li>
  <li>X ray picture did not give deformation;</li>
  <li>In wedge, Martensite regions are single variants;</li>
  <li>As the twin get finer, the inter face is compatible and strain will disappear.</li>
</ol>

<p>Reference:</p>

